提交信息: Fixed compilation with clang.  Thanks to Dmitry Tsidilin.

SSL shutdown for rtmps.  While rtmp module does not support SSL, starting from nginx 1.25.5 an SSL connection can be passed from nginx stream pass module.  Such connections should be shut down on connection closure.  An rtmps example:  rtmp {     server {         listen 1935; # rtmp         application foo {             live on;         }     } }  stream {     server {         listen 1936 ssl; # rtmps         ssl_certificate example.com.crt;         ssl_certificate_key example.com.key;         pass 127.0.0.1:1935;     } }
Added propagation of the "wildcard" flag to c->listening.  The change repeats nginx commit cb149fa03367 and is needed for stream pass module to be able to pass connections to rtmp.
Fixed null pointer dereference while reading AMF.  Thanks to Zengxian Ding.
Fixed buffer overrun after changing chunk size.  Thanks to Zengxian Ding.

Explicitly signal HE-AAC in DASH manifest  This works around an issue in the Chromium MediaSource implementation[1]. Chromium will not play a video when the audio track uses HE-AAC, unless it is explicitly signaled in the manifest.  [1]: https://code.google.com/p/chromium/issues/detail?id=370927#c3
